description: The Lebanese Hezbollah resistance movement says it carried out a suicide drone strike on Israeli soldiers positioned near the village of Yaara, saying it hit them “accurately”.
title: Hezbollah launches more attacks on northern Israel

description: The armed wing of Hamas says that its fighters managed to lure Israeli forces from a combat engineering unit into a booby-trapped tunnel, killing some and wounding others.
title: Qassam Brigades inflicting casualties in Gaza tunnel blast

description: Video posted on social media, and verified by Al Jazeera’s fact-checking unit, shows two children in Gaza collecting spilled flour from the sandy ground.
title: Hungry Palestinian children collect flour mixed with sand

description: The chief prosecutor of the International Criminal Court (ICC) has called on judges to “urgently” rule on his request for arrest warrants for Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and others linked to the war on Gaza.
title: ICC prosecutor urges judges to rule on warrants for Netanyahu, Gallant

description: Philippe Lazzarini, the commissioner-general of the UN agency for Palestine refugees (UNRWA), has said that children in Gaza are "bearing the brunt" of the war.
title: Children in Gaza 'at forefront' of war: UNRWA chief

description: Israeli forces have issued evacuation orders over the last month at an "unprecedented pace", with 13 issued since 22 July, according to a report by AP news agency.
title: Israel issuing evacuation orders at 'unprecedented pace': AP

description: Noa Argamani, an Israeli woman freed from Hamas captivity in Gaza in June, said on Friday that her injuries were caused by an Israeli air strike during her rescue operation, not by a Hamas attack.
title: Israeli captive Noa Argamani says she was wounded by Israel, not Hamas

description: TEHRAN – New Foreign Minister Abbas Araqchi said on Saturday that Iran’s response to the assassination of Hamas political bureau chief Ismail Haniyeh in Tehran will be “precise and measured”.
title: FM says Iran’s response to Haniyeh assassination will be ‘measured’

description: TEHRAN – Iran beat Libya in straight sets (25-13, 25-16, 30-28) at the 2024 FIVB Volleyball Boys’ U17 World Championship on Saturday.
title: Iran down Libya at 2024 FIVB U17 World Championship

description: TEHRAN – In a decree on Thursday, President Masoud Pezeshkian appointed Majid Ansari, a former veteran lawmaker and vice president for parliamentary affairs, as his deputy for legal affairs.
title: Majid Ansari appointed deputy president for legal affairs

description: TEHRAN - Mehdi Sanaei, a former Iranian ambassador and parliamentarian, has been appointed as the chief of the presidential office for political affairs.
title: Mehdi Sanaei named presidential office political chief

description: TEHRAN – New Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araqchi said in a televised program on Friday night that reviving the 2015 nuclear deal is not possible in its current form.
title: Reviving nuclear deal in its current form not possible: Iran’s new FM

description: BEIRUT - Many cities in the United States are witnessing massive demonstrations in solidarity with Palestine and calling for a ban on sending American weapons to the Israeli entity due to its ongoing bloody war on Gaza.
title: Muslim convert: US future might look very different as Gen Z will influence political decisions
